def: To fasten on, as armor. [Obs.] Spenser.
An orthographic projection of the sphere on the plane of themeridian, the eye being supposed at an infinite distance, and in theeast or west point of the horizon.

An order of reptiles which includes the turtles and tortoises.The body is covered by a shell consisting of an upper or dorsalshell, called the carapace, and a lower or ventral shell, called theplastron, each of which consists of several plates.
A horizontal row of corbels, with the panels or filling betweenthem; also, less properly used to include the stringcourse on them.
The act of enthralling, or state of being enthralled. SeeInthrallment.
One who persecutes, or harasses. Shak.
